[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":773},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F29\u002Fquill-overwriting-modules-with-class-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F29\u002Fquill-overwriting-modules-with-class-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F29\u002Fquill-overwriting-modules-with-class-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F29\u002Fquill-overwriting-modules-with-class-fix\u002F":749,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2023\u002F06\u002F29\u002Fquill-overwriting-modules-with-class-fix\u002F":758},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20230629\u002F1402048802\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":732,"date":733,"description":734,"extension":735,"lang":736,"meta":737,"navigation":207,"path":738,"readingMinutes":434,"seo":739,"standalone":740,"stem":741,"tags":742,"tldr":746,"updated":733,"url":747,"__hash__":748},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fquill-overwriting-modules-with-class-fix.md","Fixing the 'quill Overwriting modules\u002Fxxx with class...' Warning","1001599641",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":726},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,59,66,73,86,92,96,103,156,163,689,702,712,715,719,722],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Just a quick note here on a warning I hit while using Quill — the \"quill Overwriting modules\u002Fxxx with class...\" one — and how I got rid of it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-problem","The problem",[17,25,26],{},"I was using the VueQuill package to work with Quill, and while using it I kept getting this error in the console:",[28,29,34],"pre",{"className":30,"code":31,"language":32,"meta":33,"style":33},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","quill Overwriting modules\u002FImageUploader with class...\n","bash","",[35,36,37],"code",{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,39,42,46,50,53,56],"span",{"class":40,"line":41},"line",1,[38,43,45],{"class":44},"smYoP","quill",[38,47,49],{"class":48},"sWayO"," Overwriting",[38,51,52],{"class":48}," modules\u002FImageUploader",[38,54,55],{"class":48}," with",[38,57,58],{"class":48}," class...\n",[17,60,61],{},[62,63],"img",{"alt":64,"src":65},"quill Overwriting modules\u002FImageUploader with class...","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fjavascript\u002Fquill-qverwriting\u002F246307108-7e99cdd3-de19-4b89-bbde-120af58bf17c.png",[17,67,68,69,72],{},"The usage was actually really simple — I was just toggling the component on and off with ",[35,70,71],{},"v-if",", and that alone triggered the warning. Here's a live example if you want to see it:",[74,75,76],"ul",{},[77,78,79],"li",{},[80,81,85],"a",{"href":82,"rel":83},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodesandbox.io\u002Fs\u002Fblissful-haze-7vlsm5",[84],"nofollow","Example code",[17,87,88,89,91],{},"And it's not just ",[35,90,71],{}," — switching pages in SPA mode triggers it too. The system itself works fine, nothing breaks, but the console keeps spamming this thing and honestly it just bugged me. So here's how I fixed it.",[12,93,95],{"id":94},"the-fix","The fix",[17,97,98,99,102],{},"The fix is pretty simple. If you're registering with ",[35,100,101],{},"Quill.register('modules\u002FImageUploader', ImageUploader);",", just change it to this:",[28,104,108],{"className":105,"code":106,"language":107,"meta":33,"style":33},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","if (!Quill.imports['modules\u002FImageUploader']) {\n  Quill.register('modules\u002FImageUploader', ImageUploader);\n}\n","js",[35,109,110,132,150],{"__ignoreMap":33},[38,111,112,116,120,123,126,129],{"class":40,"line":41},[38,113,115],{"class":114},"sOudu","if",[38,117,119],{"class":118},"s8XSl"," (",[38,121,122],{"class":114},"!",[38,124,125],{"class":118},"Quill.imports[",[38,127,128],{"class":48},"'modules\u002FImageUploader'",[38,130,131],{"class":118},"]) {\n",[38,133,135,138,142,145,147],{"class":40,"line":134},2,[38,136,137],{"class":118},"  Quill.",[38,139,141],{"class":140},"scAaK","register",[38,143,144],{"class":118},"(",[38,146,128],{"class":48},[38,148,149],{"class":118},", ImageUploader);\n",[38,151,153],{"class":40,"line":152},3,[38,154,155],{"class":118},"}\n",[17,157,158,159,162],{},"If you're a VueQuill dev you might be doing it a different way. In that case I'd suggest passing things in through ",[35,160,161],{},"options",", because that's what lets you apply the fix above. Something like this:",[28,164,168],{"className":165,"code":166,"language":167,"meta":33,"style":33},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-light github-light github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cscript setup>\nimport { ref } from 'vue';\n\nimport { QuillEditor, Quill } from '@vueup\u002Fvue-quill';\nimport '@vueup\u002Fvue-quill\u002Fdist\u002Fvue-quill.snow.css';\n\nimport ImageUploader from 'quill-image-uploader';\n\nif (!Quill.imports['modules\u002FImageUploader']) {\n  Quill.register('modules\u002FImageUploader', ImageUploader);\n}\n\n\u002F**\n * Quill options\n *\u002F\nconst options = {\n  modules: {\n    ImageUploader: {\n      upload(file) {\n        return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n          \u002F\u002F ... example\n        });\n      },\n    },\n    toolbar: [\n      [{ header: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, false] }],\n      ['bold', 'italic', 'underline', 'strike'],\n      ['code', 'code-block'],\n      [{ list: 'ordered' }, { list: 'bullet' }],\n      ['image', 'link'],\n      ['clean'],\n    ],\n  },\n  placeholder: 'Type something...',\n  theme: 'snow',\n};\n\n\u003Ctemplate>\n  \u003Cdiv class=\"globalEditor\">\n    \u003CQuillEditor\n      ref=\"editorRef\"\n      :options=\"options\"\n      content-type=\"html\"\n    \u002F>\n  \u003C\u002Fdiv>\n\u003C\u002Ftemplate>\n","html",[35,169,170,186,203,209,224,234,239,254,259,274,287,292,297,304,310,316,332,338,344,359,391,397,403,409,415,421,463,490,505,523,538,548,554,560,572,583,589,594,604,624,634,645,652,663,669,6